{
  "stem": "10181.4",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We-- I didn't know it was-- nobody knew they were firing into the air, but they were, you know, to make a lot of noise shooting.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Nobody was shot.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "It was just a scare tactic.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And then we were put up in barracks, and these were completely different from Westerbork, you know, because the little food we had with us, of course, we had ate-- we consumed most of it during the-- during the trip.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "We did-- we got nothing during the trip except some water, and then when we got to Westerbork, they-- they sort of gave us-- gave us-- gave you [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Not to-- to Bergen-Belsen, I'm sorry.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "They gave you a slice of bread and some-- some soup, some-- some, which was like, you know, turnip soup, whatever it was, watery soup.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "That was the food we got when we arrived.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And you know, the men and women were separated.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "I was separated from my sister at first.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And it was-- you know, it was sort of-- it was very scary because we didn't know what was going to happen.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And we knew that the only people who were watching us now were the Germans, were the SS, nobody else, OK.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Because in Westerbork, you saw very few Germans inside the camp usually.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "Only on the days of the trains, but otherwise you didn't.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then I noticed there were some young children together in the-- in her same-- in the same barracks as she was, you know, like me, young-- young boys, so I wanted to be moved to be together with her.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she wanted me to be together with her.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And after a while, we succeeded.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, they-- they agreed that I could stay with her, you know, with-- which was a barracks of women, actually.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And for the first few weeks, except for the lack of food and the lack of sanitation-- this really was the-- the worst part.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Each barrack had sort of a washroom attached to it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Was a tap.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There was no showers.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You couldn't take a shower.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There was a wash room with a few taps and cold water, which wasn't always there, and you had to go-- if you wanted to go to the toilet, you had to go to, like, an outhouse, further away.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "That's all there was.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "You know, that's the sanitary conditions we had in Bergen-Belsen at the beginning, but it wasn't too crowded at first.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "You know.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "When we got there, the only other people in our city-- the camp was divided into several sections.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "In our section was a new section, which originally was called the-- the-- it was called a [GERMAN], which means the-- the camp with the stars because we were wearing the Jewish star.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we were wearing our own clothes.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "The rest of the camp were wearing those striped pajamas.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We were not.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We were wearing our own clothes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And originally, this-- this was considered to be an exchange camp, like I said.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And-- I said to the-- it wasn't very crowded at first.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "The only other people were some Greeks from Salonika, who ran the place, who, by the way, were very corrupt, unfortunately.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "They were Jewish, but they were in charge.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And the little food we got, they stole a lot of it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "By the time we got it, we-- there was very little left, you know, especially the bread.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Bread becomes very-- becomes very important in-- in those circumstances.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "We got very little of that.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
